<DOC><DOCNO> AP901010-0066 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NY-10-10-90 1132EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r a PM-BennettSentenced     10-10 0214</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Bennett Sentenced,0236</SECOND><HEAD>Bennett Sentenced to 12 to 25 Years</HEAD><DATELINE>BARNSTABLE, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A black man once reportedly suspectedof killing a pregnant white woman in an apparent hoax by herhusband that inflamed Boston's racial tensions has been sentencedto 12 to 25 years in prison for robbery.   William Bennett, 40, of Boston was convicted Friday inBarnstable Superior Court of robbing a Brookline video store atgunpoint Oct. 2, 1989. Judge Robert W. Banks sentenced BennettTuesday.   Bennett reportedly was identified by Charles Stuart as mostresembling the person he claimed had shot him and his pregnantwife, Carol, after jumping in their car and robbing them last Oct.23 in Boston.   Mrs. Stuart died hours after the shooting. Her prematurelydelivered son died 17 days later. Stuart was hospitalized with abullet wound.   Last January, after Stuart was implicated in the shootings, heapparently committed suicide by jumping from a bridge into theMystic River.   Authorities then said Bennett no longer was considered asuspect.   Norfolk County Assistant District Attorney Louis F. Sabadinisaid at Bennett's sentencing he had a record of 37 convictions,including shooting a police officer, shooting a taxi driver andfiring a shotgun at a police cruiser.   Bennett's lawyer said he will appeal the verdict. Bennett isalso awaiting trial on a charge of armed robbery of a Boston yogurtshop.</TEXT></DOC>